                "display"
              ],
              "color": "#35b57e"
            },
            {
              "text": " is a graphic design project "
            },
            {
              "text": "developed as",
              "color": "#f0f3f5"
            },
            {
              "text": " part of an academic assignment, inspired by the Brasilêro typeface created by Crystian Cruz. The typeface was designed based on the analysis of hundreds of hand-painted signs found in cities across Brazil, aiming to translate the impact of this popular visual culture into a digital font.\n"
